data.data: Aloo pakora is a popular street food snack served not only in Mumbai but in other parts of India as well.
Chola is a popular dish in the Indian subcontinent, especially in the Indian states of Gujarat, Rajasthan, and Goa.
Corn is a cereal grain first domesticated by indigenous peoples in southern Mexico about 10,000 years ago.
Maggi is a brand of instant noodles manufactured by Nestl√©. It was first introduced in Switzerland in 1948.
Momos are steamed or fried dumplings with a savoury filling, originating from the Himalayan region.
A thali is a platter or combination of small bowls, used for serving food in India and Nepal.
Pav Bhaji is a popular fast food dish from Maharashtra, India. It is a thick vegetable curry served with a soft bread roll.
Pizza is a savory dish usually round, flattened base of wheat-based dough topped with cheese and often various other ingredients.
Puri is a deep-fried flatbread from the Indian subcontinent, made from maida flour, and is a common staple in the Indian diet.
Rajma Rice is a dish made with red kidney beans and rice. It is a popular dish in India and Pakistan, and is also popular in the United States.
A samosa is a fried or baked pastry with a savoury filling, such as spiced potatoes, onions, peas, lentils, macaroni, noodles or eggs.
A hamburger is a sandwich consisting of one or more cooked patties of ground meat placed inside a sliced bread roll or bun.
Roti is a flatbread from the Indian subcontinent made from whole-wheat flour. It is a staple food in many regions of the Indian subcontinent.
A sweet is a confection that is typically eaten as part of dessert. It is often a sugary food, although some, such as bitter chocolate, are not.
A thali is a platter or combination of small bowls, used for serving food in India and Nepal.
KFC is an American fast food restaurant chain headquartered in Louisville, Kentucky, that specializes in fried chicken.
Pani puri, golgappa, or puchka is a popular Indian snack. It is a savoury, hollow, deep-fried ball made from a thin, maida-based batter.
Idli is a traditional breakfast food in South Indian. It is made by steaming a batter consisting of fermented black lentils and rice.
Aloo paratha is a popular Indian flatbread made with whole wheat flour, stuffed with a spiced potato filling.
Upma is a South Indian dish made from semolina, rava, or farina. It is a popular breakfast dish in South India.
Masala dosa is a type of dosa, a fermented crepe made from rice batter and black lentils.
Plain dosa is a type of dosa, a fermented crepe made from rice batter and black lentils.
Uttapam is a South Indian dish made from a fermented batter consisting of lentils and rice.
Chicken biryani is a dish of chicken and rice that has been cooked in a seasoned broth and combined with spices and herbs.
Fried rice is a dish of cooked rice that has been stir-fried in a wok or a frying pan and is usually mixed with other ingredients such as eggs, vegetables, seafood, or meat.
Chicken 65 is a spicy chicken dish from the Indian subcontinent. It is made by marinating chicken pieces in a mixture of yogurt, spices, and chili powder.
Chicken Lolli Pop is a spicy chicken dish from the Indian subcontinent. It is made by marinating chicken pieces in a mixture of yogurt, spices, and chili powder.
Chicken tikka is a dish of chunks of chicken marinated in yogurt and spices and then broiled or grilled.
Ice cream is a sweetened frozen food, It is usually made from dairy products and often combined with fruits or other ingredients and flavours.
A quesadilla is a tortilla-based dish made by grilling or baking a tortilla with cheese and other ingredients in a frying pan.
